description:
Leading manufacturer is seeking to fill entry-level Material Handler positions for its Huger, SC single-site steel coil processing plant. Responsibilities include loading/unloading raw steel materials and finished products including banding and palletizing; assisting on the press and/or slitter production lines as assigned; perform maintenance helper and other general labor actions as assigned. Successful training may lead to operator positions.

Position prerequisites:

· High school diploma/GED preferred;

· Forklift/overhead, crane operation experience preferred; on-the-job training provided.

The right person possesses:

· Dependability to be consistently at work and on time with ability to work flexible schedule of 40+ hours per week as required;

· Basic verbal/written comprehension skills;

· Basic math and measuring skills using tape measure, micrometers, calipers, and/or other measuring devices;

· Team mentality with ability to follow safety and quality procedures;

· Near/far vision; total visual field; repetitive sitting, standing, walking, driving, and/or bending; heavy lifting (up to 65 lbs) capability; multiple limb coordination.

Excellent benefits include medical with a standard PPO plan with deductibles as low as $1,500 and wellness credit up to $750; voluntary 401k plan deduction up to 12% with varying company match per quarter; voluntary dental and vision plans; telemedicine services; basic life and short term disability coverage.

EOE M/F/D/V
